{
  "texts": [
    "Following common practice in code generation, for each generation, we check if the output code can be parsed, and if there are parse errors delete lines from the end of the generated code until it parses without errors.",
    "This eliminates errors caused by truncated model outputs.Once a full set of tests have been generated, we construct the test execution context by importing all defined classes and variables that appear in the generation context.",
    "In addition, we copy all of the import statements that appear in the generation context and include them in the execution context.",
    "If the model generated any import statements for objects that are imported in the execution context, we remove the model-generated import.",
    "We address the following research questions in our evaluation:• RQ1.Performance Impact."
  ]
}